verses.text_plain: And when Abram was ninety years old and nine, the Lord appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God; walk before me, and be thou perfect.
verses.verse_html:
1And when Abram was ninety years old and nine, the Lord appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God; walk before me, and be thou perfect. ▼
▼ perfect: or, upright, or, sincere

footnotes.body_html: ▼ perfect: or, upright, or, sincere

verses.text_plain: And I will make my covenant between me and thee, and will multiply thee exceedingly.
verses.verse_html: 2And I will make my covenant between me and thee, and will multiply thee exceedingly.

tokens.text: between me and thee, and will multiply

verses.text_plain: And Abram fell on his face: and God talked with him, saying,
verses.verse_html: 3And Abram fell on his face: and God talked with him, saying,

verses.text_plain: As for me, behold, my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations.
verses.verse_html:
4As for me, behold, my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations. ▼
▼ many…: Heb. multitude of nations

tokens.text: with thee, and thou shalt be a father

footnotes.body_html: ▼ many…: Heb. multitude of nations

verses.text_plain: Neither shall thy name any more be called Abram, but thy name shall be Abraham; for a father of many nations have I made thee.
verses.verse_html:
5Neither shall thy name any more be called Abram, but thy name shall be Abraham; for a father of many nations have I made thee. ▼
▼ Abraham: that is, Father of a great multitude

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Abraham: that is, Father of a great multitude
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Abraham: that is, Father of a great multitude

verses.text_plain: And I will make thee exceeding fruitful, and I will make nations of thee, and kings shall come out of thee.
verses.verse_html: 6And I will make thee exceeding fruitful, and I will make nations of thee, and kings shall come out of thee.

verses.text_plain: And I will establish my covenant between me and thee and thy seed after thee in their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be a God unto thee, and to thy seed after thee.
verses.verse_html: 7And I will establish my covenant between me and thee and thy seed after thee in their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be a God unto thee, and to thy seed after thee.

tokens.text: between me and thee and thy seed
unto thee, and to thy seed

verses.text_plain: And I will give unto thee, and to thy seed after thee, the land wherein thou art a stranger, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession; and I will be their God.
verses.verse_html:
8And I will give unto thee, and to thy seed after thee, the land wherein thou art a stranger, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession; and I will be their God. ▼
▼ wherein…: Heb. of thy sojournings

tokens.text: unto thee, and to thy seed
and I will be their God

footnotes.body_html: ▼ wherein…: Heb. of thy sojournings

verses.text_plain: And God said unto Abraham, Thou shalt keep my covenant therefore, thou, and thy seed after thee in their generations.
verses.verse_html: 9And God said unto Abraham, Thou shalt keep my covenant therefore, thou, and thy seed after thee in their generations.

verses.text_plain: This is my covenant, which ye shall keep, between me and you and thy seed after thee; Every man child among you shall be circumcised.
verses.verse_html: 10This is my covenant, which ye shall keep, between me and you and thy seed after thee; Every man child among you shall be circumcised.

tokens.text: between me and you and thy seed

verses.text_plain: And ye shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin; and it shall be a token of the covenant betwixt me and you.
verses.verse_html: 11And ye shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin; and it shall be a token of the covenant betwixt me and you.

tokens.text: and it shall be a token

verses.text_plain: And he that is eight days old shall be circumcised among you, every man child in your generations, he that is born in the house, or bought with money of any stranger, which is not of thy seed.
verses.verse_html:
12And he that is eight days old shall be circumcised among you, every man child in your generations, he that is born in the house, or bought with money of any stranger, which is not of thy seed. ▼
▼ he that is eight…: Heb. a son of eight days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he that is eight…: Heb. a son of eight days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he that is eight…: Heb. a son of eight days

verses.text_plain: He that is born in thy house, and he that is bought with thy money, must needs be circumcised: and my covenant shall be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.
verses.verse_html: 13He that is born in thy house, and he that is bought with thy money, must needs be circumcised: and my covenant shall be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.

verses.text_plain: And the uncircumcised man child whose flesh of his foreskin is not circumcised, that soul shall be cut off from his people; he hath broken my covenant.
verses.verse_html: 14And the uncircumcised man child whose flesh of his foreskin is not circumcised, that soul shall be cut off from his people; he hath broken my covenant.

verses.text_plain: And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be.
verses.verse_html:
15And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be. ▼
▼ Sarah: that is Princess

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Sarah: that is Princess

verses.text_plain: And I will bless her, and give thee a son also of her: yea, I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of people shall be of her.
verses.verse_html:
16And I will bless her, and give thee a son also of her: yea, I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of people shall be of her. ▼
▼ she…: Heb. she shall become nations

tokens.text: also of her: yea, I will bless

footnotes.body_text: ▼ she…: Heb. she shall become nations
footnotes.body_html: ▼ she…: Heb. she shall become nations

verses.text_plain: Then Abraham fell upon his face, and laughed, and said in his heart, Shall a child be born unto him that is an hundred years old? and shall Sarah, that is ninety years old, bear?
verses.verse_html: 17Then Abraham fell upon his face, and laughed, and said in his heart, Shall a child be born unto him that is an hundred years old? and shall Sarah, that is ninety years old, bear?

tokens.text: unto him that is an hundred

verses.text_plain: And Abraham said unto God, O that Ishmael might live before thee!
verses.verse_html: 18And Abraham said unto God, O that Ishmael might live before thee!

verses.text_plain: And God said, Sarah thy wife shall bear thee a son indeed; and thou shalt call his name Isaac: and I will establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant, and with his seed after him.
verses.verse_html: 19And God said, Sarah thy wife shall bear thee a son indeed; and thou shalt call his name Isaac: and I will establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant, and with his seed after him.

verses.text_plain: And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly; twelve princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.
verses.verse_html: 20And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly; twelve princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.

tokens.text: him, and will make him fruitful

verses.text_plain: But my covenant will I establish with Isaac, which Sarah shall bear unto thee at this set time in the next year.
verses.verse_html: 21But my covenant will I establish with Isaac, which Sarah shall bear unto thee at this set time in the next year.

tokens.text: unto thee at this set time

verses.text_plain: And he left off talking with him, and God went up from Abraham.
verses.verse_html: 22And he left off talking with him, and God went up from Abraham.

verses.text_plain: And Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all that were born in his house, and all that were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham’s house; and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the selfsame day, as God had said unto him.
verses.verse_html: 23And Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all that were born in his house, and all that were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham’s house; and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the selfsame day, as God had said unto him.

verses.text_plain: And Abraham was ninety years old and nine, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.
verses.verse_html: 24And Abraham was ninety years old and nine, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.

verses.text_plain: And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.
verses.verse_html: 25And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.

verses.text_plain: In the selfsame day was Abraham circumcised, and Ishmael his son.
verses.verse_html: 26In the selfsame day was Abraham circumcised, and Ishmael his son.

verses.text_plain: And all the men of his house, born in the house, and bought with money of the stranger, were circumcised with him.
verses.verse_html: 27And all the men of his house, born in the house, and bought with money of the stranger, were circumcised with him.
